Hi, Adriene.

First of all I would like to Thank You for posting these videos. The 30 day Yoga Journey came to me at the right time.
Second - today was a very special day due to the discovery I noticed. I know for a fact that my spine is crooked and that leads to several issues, on of them being often headache, dizziness, black outs. I know that my 3td to 5th vertebrae are a offset since I was a kid.
I have noticed that my face stays white after moderate walks or runs, which tells me that the blood circulation to the head isn't good. I tend to get a little redness in my cheeks only after intense workouts.
So today when doing Sweet 16 it really turned out super sweet because of the sensations I had. When doing One-Legged Tadasana I felt a deep stretch, did 5 breaths on on leg once I lowered my leg and stood in the Mountain pose my head was dizzy like crazy, but in a good way, I couldn't see for a sec and had a powerful heat wave. I was a little familiar with the feeling but never been able to get to it deliberately. So then I repeated the same pose with the other leg and same thing happened, then switched again - same thing happened. I did 5 times each leg and same sensations happened. I felt like I had released some old entrenched tension that I have had for years - so again THANK YOU!
I will keep continue the Journey and hopefully release more tension points to get to a better version of myself!

Paldies!

p.s. I Skipped day 14 due to my lazy ass, did day 14 and day 15 on day 15 :)

M

Yoga still isn't something that I'm sure is for me. I like the flexibility and strength I gain, but a lot of the mental components don't resonate with me. Yet I still can't stop myself from returning to Adriene's videos, particularly these 30 day January journeys. This is (by far) the furthest I've ever made it through a series, and I'm shocked at how 20-25 minutes has gone from feeling like an eternity to feeling like a warm up. 

I'll look up at the screen expecting to find that we're at the halfway point, and realize that there's only four minutes left and we're winding down for the day. When I started, I had to split day one into two parts, and now I'm looking at the rest of the videos on this channel to get another practice in because 20 minutes doesn't feel like enough. 

Even without being great at the meditative aspects, there is so much to be gained from following along with a series like this. It's nuts lol
